geneSummary: AR (androgen receptor), a transcription factor, is most frequently altered in advanced or castration-resistant prostate cancer.

mutationEffect.description: The AR Q58_Q59insL mutation is located in the amino-terminal domain of the protein. This mutation was found in the germline of an individual with minor androgen insensitivity syndrome. Expression of this mutation in a simian cell line demonstrated that it is likely inactivating as measured by decreased AR transcriptional activity compared to wildtype (PMID: 25500996).

variantSummary: The AR L57_Q58insLQQQQQQQQ alteration is likely neutral.
